  <h2>200 Level Classes</h2>

  <!-- Justified paragraph (rubric requirement) -->
  <p class="justify">
    The 200-level courses introduce students to foundational concepts in digital arts,
    audio production, programming, and web design. These classes establish the technical
    and creative base required for advanced coursework in the major.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>201</strong> – Basic Skills in the Digital Arts</li>
    <li><strong>202</strong> – Foundations: Audio Theory</li>
    <li><strong>203</strong> – Foundations: Recording and Sampling</li>
    <li><strong>204</strong> – Foundations: Music Concepts</li>
    <li><strong>208</strong> – Audio Production I</li>
    <li><strong>231</strong> – Web Design and Development</li>
    <li><strong>232</strong> – Computer Programming for Creatives</li>
    <li><strong>240</strong> – Sound Design I</li>
    <li><strong>260</strong> – Arts Technology Performance Studio</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>300 Level Classes</h2>

  <!-- Centered paragraph (rubric requirement) -->
  <p class="center">
    300-level courses focus on advanced creative development, production techniques,
    and interdisciplinary applications of technology in the arts.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>303</strong> – Advanced Web Design and Development</li>
    <li><strong>320</strong> – Programming Dynamic Media</li>
    <li><strong>330</strong> – Web Video</li>
    <li><strong>340</strong> – Sound Design II</li>
    <li><strong>345</strong> – Sequencing and Digital Audio</li>
    <li><strong>351</strong> – Game Design I</li>
    <li><strong>354</strong> – User Experience Design for Games</li>
    <li><strong>377</strong> – Motion Graphics</li>
  </ul>

